node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
@clintmwallace is revealing what it REALLY takes to build a 7-Figure Amazon FBA Business from his own experience in doing $100k/m from his Amazon business.
Follow 👉🏼 @clintmwallace
Follow 👉🏼 @clintmwallace
Follow 👉🏼 @clintmwallace for the BEST Amazon business advice.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace How built a multi 7-figure amazon business after getting laid off from my job. You might want to save this [THREAD]'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I don't want to bore you with my story so I'll keep it short. I got laid off from my job in 2017 and there was nothing could do about it. started selling on Amazon because| needed to put food on the table and had a kid on the way.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I only ended up using $3k to start. I bought a course from some guy with a Lambo and it was clear that he didn't sell on Amazon. It didn't help much and had to learn everything from scratch.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace Now to the fun part. I had three products fail before had one successful product. I took the every ast dollar made from that product and reinvested it back into the business. My family was even surviving off of credit card points at one point.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I almost completely lost my business a few months later. I tried launching 2 products, and ran out of cash to buy inventory. I had to let go of both of my new products and refilled the inventory on my first product. I got too greedy and paid the price.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace Since then, I've learned my lesson. Never scale too quickly and always take things one step at a time. I've beer building this business for 3 years now and still reinvest 40% of my profits back into the business. Even after 3 years, it's barely gotten to the $100k/m profit point.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace So what lessons can you take away from this? 1. Don't scale too quickly. 2. Don't overestimate your abilities. 3. Take things one step at a time. 4. Chasing short-term wins can hurt you long-term. 5. Learn from others who have done it, but always look for ways to improve.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I've built my Amazon FBA ousiness to $250k/ rev and 100k/m profit. If wasn't so focused on getting rich quick when started, I'd probably be at $500k/m. Hopefully you don't make the same mistakes that made.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace P.S. Here's a bonus if you've made it this far. The products that had to let go of when scaled too quickly are... Baby shower decorations and felt letter boards. Follow me if you want to learn more about Amazon FBA!'.
